{{main|2022 Australian federal election}}
{{see also|Results of the 2022 Australian federal election (House of Representatives)|Results of the 2022 Australian federal election (Senate)}}
At the previous election in May 2022, the Australian Labor Party|Labor Party, led by Anthony Albanese, formed government after nine years in opposition, winning 77 seats in the House of Representatives, enough for a two-seat majority. The Liberal Party of Australia|Liberal–National Party of Australia|National Coalition (Australia)|Coalition that had previously governed won only 58 seats and went into Opposition (Australia)|opposition. The Crossbencher|crossbench, made up of other parties and Independent politician|independents, expanded to 16 seats; ten held by independents (including seven held by a loose grouping of teal independents), four by the Australian Greens|Greens, and one each by Centre Alliance and Katter's Australian Party.
